parameters:
"Yes, so far there are no problems. Nothing happened
yesterday either."

"Also, I'll be entering the cave from today, so it might be
difficult to contact me, but don't worry."
"Well then, I'll get in touch again if anything happens."

"(I thought there were measures in place, but when I try to
tell Suelle and the others about this, I end up saying
something different than what I intended.)"

"(Moreover, even when I try to return to town, my body
becomes immobile the moment I attempt to act.)"

"(I tried a few other things I could think of, but none of
them worked.)"

"(This means it's not a type that restricts specific words
or actions, but rather it reacts to my very will to defy
Maroges.)"

"(So no matter how much I strategize to break the current
situation, my own self, knowing the intent, ends up
interfering.)"

"(It's troublesome, but they wouldn't leave me so
defenseless without taking such measures, would they?)"

Tina takes a brief breath and organizes her current
situation.

"(The question is when was I subjected to the brainwashing
hypnosis skill...)"

Tina is a high-ranking swordsman. She can easily repel
ordinary brainwashing hypnosis techniques.

Furthermore, her unique skill "Full Body" allows her to
counter any external attacks that are outside of
consciousness.

Yet Tina, with such a foolproof skill, didn't even notice
that she was being brainwashed.

"(No, there's only one thing that comes to mind, that chill
I felt during that contract of servitude...)"

"(Come to think of it, such an unnatural chill. Under normal
circumstances, I wouldn't have dismissed it as a mere
mistake...)"

"(It's better to assume that I was already brainwashed at
that time.)"

"(And now I can remember. At that time, they were
indoctrinating me with the creepy false common sense of a
lady knight's etiquette.)"
Tina recalls what happened yesterday and grimaces.
"(So my information has been completely leaked, huh?)"

"(But if it really is a contract of servitude, then this
brainwashing technique isn't ordinary—it's a lost
technique.)"
"That means it's an ancient technique, right?"

Ancient techniques are fundamentally different from modern
ones; they were used in the past.

Nowadays, the techniques themselves are not passed down,
only mentioned in historical documents.

However, if it's a technique with different principles, then
even using current skills, I can't formulate a
countermeasure.

If it's something that can't be dealt with even with Full
Body, then being able to react automatically is meaningless.

"(But there's no way someone like Maroges could use an
ancient technique.)"

"(If there was someone else involved who could truly use
ancient techniques, that would be a tremendous problem.)"

After pondering for a while, Tina decides that rather than
the nature of the technique, it's more important to focus on
her current situation and how to overcome it.

Suppressing her discomfort, she vividly recalls yesterday's
events and Maroges's words.

"(Come to think of it, Maroges mentioned training both my
mind and body yesterday. Brainwashing and training the
mind?)"

"(Just like when they indoctrinated me with the so-called
etiquette of a lady knight, they could make me forget the
actions that took place that day.)"

"(In other words, if there was a need to risk retaining my
memories and revert my consciousness from the
brainwashing...)"

"(If they consider that they can't train the mind while it's
brainwashed,)"

"(Doesn't that mean they can't fully brainwash unless they
break the spirit and remove the barriers?)"

"(If the contract of servitude is a temporary technique
within a set period, then the brainwashing would also
disappear once the contract expires, right?)"

"(So could it be that complete brainwashing is about
breaking the spirit entirely so that the brainwashed state
is maintained even after the contract ends?)"

Tina constructs the logic of brainwashing and conditions in
her head. The next thing to consider is a countermeasure.

"(If the activation condition for this brainwashing hypnosis
was brought about by the contract of servitude, then by
completing this request...)"

"(Or if it becomes invalid when the three weeks are up and
Selphie cancels the request...)"

"(Although it's still conjecture, I think there's a good
chance it's possible.)"

Then there are two victory conditions. One is the completion
of the request. The other is for Tina to endure without
breaking for three weeks.

"(However, the fact that things have progressed this far
means that if I can't endure and am completely
brainwashed...)"

"(Whether the request is completed or cancelled, I'll remain
brainwashed... This hypothesis also becomes more credible.)"

And so, Maroges will not let the mission end without
incident. There must be other traps set.

"(Even so... even if they try to prolong the mission, three
weeks is the limit. If I can endure that long, there's a
high possibility that this spell will be broken.)"

"(The rate of brainwashing erosion shouldn't be too high
yet. If I keep my consciousness clear and stay alert to even
the slightest anomalies, I believe I'm at a stage where I
can deal with it.)"

"(For now, I have no choice but to follow Maroges while
looking for an opportunity to complete the request or find a
way to break the brainwashing hypnosis.)"

"(It's okay... If I keep my spirits up, I can get through
this.)"
